to the editor in decrying the decline of marriage william safire column may 21 manages to belittle the one group of people who actually want to marry but ca n't the gay couples i know are not just hanging out together as mr safire puts it we are raising children together caring for our homes naming each other in insurance policies wills and powers of attorney signing up for domestic partner benefits and taking whatever other steps we can think of to strengthen and solidify our lifetime commitments i look forward to the day when gay couples can share the same benefits and responsibilities that mr safire and his wife of 40 years probably take for granted marcie horowitz westfield nj may 22 2001

